    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-08-01</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-09-26T21:40:25Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Amends the Internal Revenue Code to exclude any amount derived from an investment of federal grant or related state matching amounts made in connection with any revolving fund established under the Federal Water Pollution Control Act or the Safe Drinking Water Act from a determination of whether a bond is an arbitrage bond (thus allowing states to retain arbitrage earnings from state revolving loan funds). </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>A bill to amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to provide that amounts derived from Federal grants and State matching funds in connection with revolving funds established in accordance with the Federal Water Pollution Control Act and the Safe Drinking Water Act will not be treated as proceeds or replacement proceeds for purposes of section 148 of such Code.</title>
